<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 5:51PM CDT  by NWS Goodland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Thomas,
northern Sheridan, southeastern Rawlins and southern Decatur Counties
through 615 PM CDT...
At 551 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Rexford, or 19 miles northeast of Colby, moving east
at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Selden around 610 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for northwestern
Kansas.</instruction>
